## How to Convert PDF to EPUB on Mac, Windows, and Online (2026)

PDF and EPUB serve fundamentally different purposes. PDFs preserve exact formatting — making them perfect for print-ready documents — while EPUB reflows text to fit any screen size, giving readers a comfortable experience on ereaders, phones, and tablets.

If you've been wondering **how to convert PDF to EPUB**, you're in the right place. This guide covers every method available in 2026: desktop software for Mac and Windows, and free online converters.

---

## Why Convert PDF to EPUB?

PDF files are "fixed layout" — they look the same on every device, but they don't adapt. On a small ereader screen, that means constant zooming, panning, and a poor reading experience.

EPUB is the opposite. It's a "reflowable" format, meaning:

- Text adjusts to fit any screen size automatically
- Font size is adjustable by the reader
- Bookmarking and highlights work properly
- File sizes are typically smaller

The result is a much more comfortable reading experience, especially on dedicated ereaders like Kindle, Kobo, or Kobo Clara.

