## Method 2: Calibre (Free — Mac, Windows, Linux)

[Calibre](https://calibre-ebook.com/) is the gold standard for ebook management and conversion. It's free, open-source, and handles even difficult PDFs better than most paid tools.

### Step-by-Step: PDF to EPUB with Calibre

**Step 1: Download and Install Calibre**

Download Calibre from [calibre-ebook.com](https://calibre-ebook.com/). The installer is available for macOS, Windows, and Linux.

**Step 2: Add Your PDF**

Click the "Add books" button (top left, looks like a green folder with a plus sign) and select your PDF file.

**Step 3: Select and Convert**

Right-click on your added book, then select **"Convert books" → "Convert individually"**.

In the output format dropdown at the top right of the conversion dialog, select **EPUB**.

**Step 4: Tweak Options (Optional)**

Navigate through the left panel options:

- **Metafloppy** — Set your book title and author
- **Page setup** — Choose input and output page margins
- **Heuristics** — Enable "OCR the input" if you have a scanned PDF
- **Table of Contents** — Let Calibre attempt auto-detection of chapters

**Step 5: Convert**

Click **OK** at the bottom right. Calibre will process the PDF and add the EPUB to your library.

**Step 6: Transfer to Your Device**

Connect your ereader via USB and use Calibre's device icon to send the EPUB directly, or right-click the book and choose "Open containing folder" to find the file manually.

### Calibre PDF-to-EPUB Limitations

Calibre handles PDF text extraction well for text-based PDFs. Scanned PDFs require OCR, which Calibre can perform but results vary depending on scan quality. Complex PDF layouts (multi-column, tables, sidebars) often don't convert cleanly — in those cases, manual editing of the EPUB may be needed.

