## Frequently Asked Questions

### Does converting PDF to EPUB lose formatting?

Some formatting will change. EPUB reflows text, so fixed layouts won't stay identical. Fonts, page numbers, and complex graphics may not transfer perfectly. Headings, paragraphs, lists, and basic styling typically preserve well.

### Can I convert PDF to EPUB on my phone?

Yes. Several apps can convert PDF to EPUB directly on iOS or Android, including **Calibre Companion** (paired with Calibre on your computer) and various file converter apps available in the App Store and Google Play.

### Is there a free PDF to EPUB converter?

Yes. **Calibre** is the best free option and works on Mac, Windows, and Linux. Online tools vary in quality — be cautious with free online converters that require uploading your document, as privacy may be a concern.

### What about Kindle? Can I send an EPUB directly?

Amazon Kindle does not natively support EPUB files. You'll need to convert EPUB to MOBI or AZW3 before sending to a Kindle. Calibre handles this automatically when you connect a Kindle. Alternatively, send the EPUB to your Kindle email address — Amazon converts it during delivery.

